# Documentation logging (mandatory)

Read `memory/00_START_HERE.md` for the One-Sentence Policy. This rule enforces it on every code change.

## 1. CHANGELOG — required after code changes

**Trigger:** You successfully add, modify, or delete any file under the repo **except** pure documentation-only edits confined to `memory/` (this rule itself, audits, etc.). Code paths include at minimum: `frontend/`, `scripts/`, `.github/`.

**Action:** Immediately open `memory/CHANGELOG.md` and append a **dated entry** (today’s date) under the May 21, 2026 baseline. Each entry must include:

- **What changed** — one or two sentences, plain English
- **Files** — paths touched
- **Verification** — how you confirmed it (build, grep, manual check)
- **Caveats** — `PARTIAL` if stubs, placeholders, or user-only steps remain

Do not edit `memory/CHANGELOG-legacy-pre-2026-05-21.md` for new work.

**GA4:** If event names or params changed in code, update `memory/GA4_EVENTS.md` in the same pass.

## 2. ROADMAP — required when work is incomplete or new scope appears

**Trigger:** The coding task introduces any of:

- A new structural requirement (deps, env vars, migrations, CI)
- A known bug or regression left unfixed
- A feature intentionally incomplete (placeholder data, stub URL, missing sitewide rollout)

**Action:** Open `memory/ROADMAP.md` and add or update an **open** item in the correct P-tier section or Active execution queue. Use existing ID style when possible (`P1.10`, `C3`, `SEC-1`). Do **not** add “✅ SHIPPED” rows to ROADMAP — shipped work belongs only in CHANGELOG.

**When something fully ships:** Remove its open row from ROADMAP (do not strike through or leave duplicate open items).

## 3. Completion gate — strict

You are **forbidden** from telling the user a programming task is **Complete**, **Finished**, or **Done** until all of the following are true:

1. **Code** — changes are saved and verified (build/lint/grep as appropriate)
2. **CHANGELOG** — dated entry reflects the actual code state (including `PARTIAL` caveats)
3. **ROADMAP** — no stale open item for work you just finished; new gaps recorded if any remain
4. **Reconciliation** — event names match `GA4_EVENTS.md`; no claim of “shipped” without file-path evidence

If you only changed `memory/*.md` with no code diff, say **documentation updated** — not “feature shipped.”

## Quick checklist (end of every code task)

```
[ ] Code verified
[ ] memory/CHANGELOG.md — dated entry added
[ ] memory/ROADMAP.md — open items added/removed to match reality
[ ] memory/GA4_EVENTS.md — updated if analytics code changed
[ ] Ready to report complete to user
```
